description.p:
(1) determining and displaying the critical angle at which a vehicle is likely to overturn based on input vehicle and load information;


(2) continuously monitoring and displaying the angle of the net dynamic forces on the vehicle during negotiation of the curve, including forces resulting from crosswind pressure, vehicle vertical acceleration, and vehicle lateral acceleration, for comparison with the displayed critical angle;


(3) automatically comparing the net dynamic force vector with the critical angle and alerting the operator of the vehicle when the net dynamic force vector approaches the critical angle; and


(4) enabling the operator of a vehicle to easily determine appropriate speeds for negotiating the curve based on the critical angle and the geometry of the curve, based on posted curve radii and bank information.
